# GitHub CODEOWNERS for ArchLucid (repo: joefrancisGA/ArchiForge)
#
# Purpose
#   - Auto-assigns reviewers when a PR touches matching paths.
#   - When combined with branch-protection "Require review from Code Owners",
#     listed owners must approve before merge.
#   - GitHub Copilot code review (auto-request) runs *in addition to* the humans
#     listed here; CODEOWNERS does not control Copilot. See
#     docs/runbooks/COPILOT_CODE_REVIEW_SETUP.md for the Copilot side.
#
# Syntax
#   <pattern>  <owner1> <owner2> ...
#   - Patterns follow .gitignore-style globbing.
#   - Later patterns override earlier patterns for the same path.
#   - Owners are GitHub usernames (@user) or teams (@org/team-name).
#
# Add teammates by appending their handle to the relevant line.
# Today this repo has a single maintainer, so @joefrancisGA is the default
# owner everywhere. Do NOT remove the catch-all `*` entry below — without it,
# files not matched by any other pattern would have no owner.

# Default owner for everything not matched below.
*                                       @joefrancisGA

# --- Security-sensitive areas (require maintainer review) ---------------------

# Anything in .github/ controls CI, security scanning, branch protection docs,
# Copilot review configuration, and CodeQL. Touch with care.
/.github/                               @joefrancisGA

# Terraform — infra changes can affect public exposure, identity, and cost.
# Per workspace rules: SMB/445 must never be public; storage uses private endpoints.
/infra/                                 @joefrancisGA

# Master SQL DDL — single-file-per-database rule means changes here ripple.
ArchLucid.sql                           @joefrancisGA
**/ArchLucid.sql                        @joefrancisGA

# Historical migrations 001–028 are immutable per rename guardrails. Owner
# review is a backstop in case someone tries to edit them.
/migrations/                            @joefrancisGA

# Authentication, authorization, RLS, and tenant scope.
**/Authority/                           @joefrancisGA
**/Auth/                                @joefrancisGA
**/Rls/                                 @joefrancisGA
**/MultiTenant*                         @joefrancisGA

# CodeQL custom queries (log-sanitizer barrier — guards against secret leaks).
/.github/codeql/                        @joefrancisGA

# Rename checklist + runbooks (operational guardrails).
/docs/ARCHLUCID_RENAME_CHECKLIST.md     @joefrancisGA
/docs/runbooks/                         @joefrancisGA

# Cursor rules — these shape AI behavior across the team.
/.cursor/rules/                         @joefrancisGA
/.github/copilot-instructions.md        @joefrancisGA
